    116          /**
    117           *  @brief		It checks if Rapid Advance Option is active and if a request to advance step has been made.
    118           *  			It is called in RUN_ENTRY but it has no effect if RUN_ENTRY is called inside EventStart(),
    119           *  			because it is preceded by the macro START in which DoorMonitor__ResetStepAdvRequest() is called,
    120           *  			that resets any pending request of step advancing. So a step advance request can be executed only
    121           *  			if RUN_ENTRY is called inside EventResume() (in other words, if the previous state is STATE_SUPERVISOR_PAUSE).
    122           *  			Note that calling this routine inside macro RESUME wouldn't work, because when RESUME is called
    123           *  			Supervisor_Data[Current_Compartment].State is still STATE_SUPERVISOR_PAUSE, so Supervisor__SetStep()
    124           *  			has no effect.
    125           *  @Warning	Based on the considerations above, working of this routine strongly depends on the architecture
    126           *  			of the calls of the Supervisor's macros.
    127           *
    128           */

